class pynext.gateway.DiscordWebSocket(user, client, chunk_guilds, chunk_channels, debug_events)[source]#

Bases: object

DiscordWebSocket class supports a single connection to the Discord gateway.

Parameters:

  • user (SelfBot) – Selfbot assigned to the connection.

  • client (PynextClient) – Pynext client.

  • chunk_guilds (bool) – Whether the client should chunk selfbot guilds.

  • chunk_channels (bool) – Whether the client should chunks guild channels.

  • debug_events (bool) – Whether the client should run debug events such as: on_websocket_raw_receive.

user#

Selfbot that is supposed to be connected to the gateway.

websocket#

Aiohttp websocket connection.

dispatcher#

Client master dispatcher.

connected#

Asyncio event that determines whether the selfbot has been connected.

latency#

Websocket latency value.

Parameters:

request (dict[str, Any]) – Prepared request to be sent to change the presence of the selfbot.

async change_voice_state(guild_id, channel_id, self_mute=False, self_deaf=False)[source]#

A method to change the voice state on the guild.

Parameters:

  • guild_id (int) – Id of the server on which we are changing the state.

  • channel_id (Optional[int]) – Id of the voice channel on which we are changing the state.

  • self_mute (bool) – Whether the selfbot should have a muted microphone.

  • self_deaf (bool) – Whether selfbot should have a muted sound.
